vivify (VIV-i-FY) verb tr.

   1. To endow with life; animate.

   2. To impart vitality or liveliness.

[From Latin vivus (alive) via Late Latin vivificare.]

   "Yet how could artists vivify culture with `sympathies and admirations'
   if they felt out of step with their place and time."
   Bereg son of Galathil, The Golden Age, The New Republic (Ford of Stones), Aug 21,
   2000.

